cairo
-------------------------------------------
Cairo is a vector graphics library with cross-device output
support. Currently supported output targets include the X Window
System and in-memory image buffers. PostScript and PDF file output is
planned. Cairo is designed to produce identical output on all output
media while taking advantage of display hardware acceleration when
available (eg. through the X Render Extension).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  libX11_6-1.0.0-2
  libXrender1-0.9.0.2-1
  libfontconfig1-2.2.2-1
  libglitz1-0.5.3-1
  libpng12-1.2.8-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  autoconf2.5-2.59-3
  automake1.9-1.9.6-1
  binutils-20050610-1
  cygport-0.1.6-1
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  gtk-doc-1.4-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.20-2
  make-3.80-1
  pkg-config-0.20-1
  sed-4.1.4-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://cairographics.org/

Canonical download:
  http://cairographics.org/snapshots/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack cairo-1.0.2-1-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  ./cairo-1.0.2-1.sh all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cairo-1.0.2-1-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/cairo-1.0.2-1.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/cairo-doc-1.0.2-1.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libcairo2-1.0.2-1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

